# Working with Modulor (agent-native CAD)

- Install once: `pip install modulor`. One document = one `.json` file.
- Execute JSON command batches: `modulor run model.json script.json`
  (or `-` for stdin). Batches are atomic; errors are structured JSON with
  a `hint` field — read it and resend the fixed batch.
- Discover the API at runtime, never guess: `modulor ops` lists all 71
  ops; `modulor ops add_wall` shows params, defaults and an example.
- Verify visually and numerically after building:
  `{"op":"render","path":"check.png","labels":true}` then look at the
  image; `{"op":"measure",...}`, `{"op":"validate"}`.
- Prefer tags over ids in selectors: create with `"tag":"plate"`, select
  with `{"tags":["plate"]}`.
- Numeric params accept expressions: `"bay*3"`, `"level_top('L2')"`,
  `"grid_x('B')"` — combine with `recipe_set` + `regenerate` for
  parametric models.
- Conventions: Z up, degrees CCW, mm by default; closed shapes can be
  extruded/lofted/swept; booleans consume inputs unless `keep:true`.
- Exports by extension: .dxf .svg (drawings) / .glb .stl .obj (meshes) /
  .ifc (semantic BIM: walls with openings, storeys, grids, spaces).
- Import existing drawings: `{"op":"import_dxf","path":"plan.dxf"}`.
